<TEXT>
following a successful practice 
countdown with discoverys five astronauts nasa officials said 
they hope this month to launch the first space shuttle since the 
challenger disaster nearly three years ago 
you have a feeling this train is about to leave the station 
and were about to get on board astronaut mike lounge said after 
thursdays exercise the last major milestone before discoverys 
launch 
we clearly demonstrated that were ready to pick up the count 
for real i hope that we will be able to do that by the end of the 
month kennedy space center director forrest s mccartney told 
the launch team 
the test concluded three days of training here for the 
astronauts they flew back to houstons johnson space center where 
they planned to concentrate on flight simulator work between now 
and launch time 
lounge and discovery commander rick hauck will return here for 
launch and flight readiness reviews tuesday and wednesday with key 
shuttle managers nasa is expected to announce a launch date after 
wednesdays meeting 
officials have been discussing a date from sept 26 to sept 29 
hauck lounge and the other crew members dick covey george 
nelson and dave hilmers climbed aboard discovery for the final two 
hours of the practice count pulling switches testing 
communications and monitoring systems just as they will on launch 
day 
the only problem was with a ground communications link between 
the launch control center and the spacecraft it was corrected but 
delayed completion of the countdown 34 minutes 
during their fourday missions the astronauts are scheduled to 
deploy a communications satellite test new spaceship systems and 
conduct science and technology experiments 
the shuttle fleet has been grounded since the jan 28 1986 
challenger explosion that killed all seven crew members 73 seconds 
after liftoff 
