an agriculture department personnel specialist 
says there are about 2000 different kinds of jobs in the 
department held by 122900 employees including 35 farmers 
brad foote of the usda office of personnel says the 122900 
employees include all fulltime parttime and temporary workers 
located throughout the united states and in foreign agricultural 
posts 
foote described the departments job situation in usda news a 
monthly newsletter for employees 
the job list includes more than 14500 forestry technicians 
6000 clerktypists 4900 soil conservationists 3500 
secretaries 3100 biological technicians and 1300 accounting 
technicians 
also he said the department has a number of rather out of 
the ordinary positions such as six model makers whose jobs are 
to develop prototype models for use in research and scientific 
experiments 
foote said others include four tree trimmers four industrial 
hygienists three aircraft mechanics two boat operators and one 
sewing machine operator 
