said 
petri and sen rudy boschwitz rminn have introduced bills 
that would expand the earned income tax credit to which poor 
working families are entitled they say that such a change would 
help lowincome workers more efficiently than a minimum wage 
increase which they say would have more of an impact on workers in 
the middle class 
currently lowincome workers are allowed tax credits of up to 
874 a break that petri and boschwitz would expand by for the 
first time increasing it according to the size of workers families 
