<TEXT>
thousands of ethnic germans from 
eastern europe are coming to west germany and state officials are 
seeking ways to cope with the burden on schools housing and social 
services 
several state leaders met friday with federal officials to 
discuss the crisis they are demanding the government pay a larger 
share of the added costs 
more than 200000 people almost all of them ethnic germans are 
expected to arrive in west germany this year from the soviet union 
poland and other east european countries the same number is 
expected next year 
although german by heritage many do not speak the german 
language 
government facilities have long since overflowed and many 
newcomers are housed in gymnasiums and other makeshift quarters 
the influx is in large part the result of a change of policy in 
many east bloc countries although the bonn government has worked 
for years to gain permission for ethnic germans to emigrate it was 
not prepared for the response 
weve got to get these people out of gymnasiums herbert 
schnoor interior minister for north rhein westfalia state told 
reporters at a press conference in bonn 
schnoor was among the state officials who met with government 
leaders friday 
the federal government has proposed a 450 million program to 
build 30000 new apartments state leaders are demanding a 19 
billion program to build 54000 new apartments 
these people are being found housing but not in the manner we 
would like schnoor said 
he said the government must provide an additional 405 million 
in emergency help 
without this money we cant begin to solve the problem 
schnoor said 
schnoor said chancellor helmut kohl was receptive to the 
suggestions and that he made it clear that solutions would not 
break down because of financial disputes 
the majority of the ethnic germans are from poland and the 
soviet union government officials said the soviet union alone has 
granted exit visas to 15715 ethnic germans this year 
bavarian interior minister max streibl said the federal 
government should pay twothirds of the costs leaving the states 
to pay the final third 
three government crisis groups have been formed and the 
interior ministry is developing an overall program in conjunction 
with the housing ministry the chancellors office is working on a 
program of language instruction and job placement for the 
immigrants 
