<TEXT>
a proposed law to further limit imports of 
textiles apparel and shoes also will lead to increased costs and 
tighter supplies for the nations retailers and higher prices for 
consumers storeowners say 
the bill now before the senate opens up a lot of problems 
said david jackson a spokesman for the apparel retailer gap inc 
under the bill this years textile and apparel imports would be 
frozen at 1987 levels and growth would be limited to 1 percent 
annually in succeeding years 
that would create what the retail industry calls sourcing 
problems stores will have a harder time obtaining merchandise 
it opens up a whole parade of horribles for us said jackson 
rob longendyke a spokesman for spiegel inc the catalog 
retailer that also owns the apparel retailers eddie bauer and 
