<TEXT>
the nations big three automakers on friday 
announced they had formed a partnership for joint research into 
plastics in car structures 
for years general motors corp ford motor co and chrysler 
corp have toyed with the moving from metal to plastic bodies in 
cars and light trucks gm used plastic body parts in its pontiac 
fiero which it recently stopped making gms chevrolet corvette 
has had a fiberglas body for years 
the three companies said in a joint statement two people from 
each corporation would form the board of the new consortium 
each of the car makers will share with the others through the 
partnership its precompetitive or generic research data 
into polymerbased composites gm ford and chrysler will determine 
by themselves what data each company will show the others for the 
next 12 years 
officials of each of corporation said friday the research would 
include structural plastics 
what they are looking at are composite materials said don 
postma a spokesman for the gm technical center in warren mich 
the advantages to the composites are the combination of light 
weight and considerably more strength not to mention corrosion 
resistance 
it is the kind of strength factors that lead composites to be 
considered for vehicle frames and loadcarrying members of the 
cars he added 
the goal is to develop technologies to allow plastic 
structural parts for cars chrysler spokesman ben dunn said 
the applications that could revolutionize the industry are the 
major body structural components and that is the goal of this 
research 
its a very positive step that theyve taken said joseph 
miller director of engineering materials for du pont automotive 
products of troy mich its a recognition by them of potential 
future benefit to composite polymers used in primary structural 
applications 
without elaborating miller said weve got some confidential 
programs with all the car companies with fenders and 
quarterpanels du pont is a major supplier of plastics to the 
automobile industry 
dunn postma and joyce stilton of ford each said it was too 
early to say how much money or staff would be involved in the joint 
venture each of the big three would take on onethird of the 
financial burden the companies said 
the consortium to share the research is the first such agreement 
among the big three and falls under guidelines of the national 
cooperative research act passed in 1984 
</TEXT>
